{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2670, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2670", "issue_numbers": [2669], "base_commit": "bab84c42dbdf30d3034bedb02335948abd8ac9d9", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Project.panel/ptools.stack/Links.pulldown/Create Workset For Linked Element.pushbutton/script.py b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Project.panel/ptools.stack/Links.pulldown/Create Workset For Linked Element.pushbutton/script.py\nindex 08329dd4dd..aed2712c54 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Project.panel/ptools.stack/Links.pulldown/Create Workset For Linked Element.pushbutton/script.py\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Project.panel/ptools.stack/Links.pulldown/Create Workset For Linked Element.pushbutton/script.py\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n+# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-\n from pyrevit import revit, DB\n from pyrevit import script\n from pyrevit import forms\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: encoding issue, create worksets per link\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nWE USE PYREVIT 2023 , when we try to use this functionnality it breaks with this message\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1534e2df-fd06-436a-855a-ad94fa33b398)\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nSee image below\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nNot relevant\nWindows 11, revit 2023\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Due to accents in french.\nFixed by #2670\nMerci pour le rapport @bobbieqc \n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/d04f0b2761d8b61ed7997b362dcf07c031493c14"], "created_at": "2025-05-16T06:35:20Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2683, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2683", "issue_numbers": [2678], "base_commit": "a62ca46050efe21a207551adec9fcbfe2ec9c3ac", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/script.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/script.py\nindex 68a238d39a..fe300d922f 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/script.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/script.py\n@@ -717,7 +717,7 @@ def element_ids(self):\n                                   file_ext=DATAFEXT,\n                                   add_cmd_name=False)\n \n-    with open(data_file, 'w') as dfile:\n+    with open(data_file, \"wb\") as dfile:\n         pickle.dump(data, dfile)\n \n \n@@ -774,7 +774,7 @@ def element_ids(self):\n                                   file_ext=DATAFEXT,\n                                   add_cmd_name=False)\n \n-    with open(data_file, 'r') as dfile:\n+    with open(data_file, 'rb') as dfile:\n         return pickle.load(dfile)\n \n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Error trying to use \"Paste State\" with IronPython 3.4.2\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nTested in Revit 2024, when copying using \"Copy State\" and pasting to another view the listet error appears\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nFile \"pickle.py\", line 1548, in _load\n File \"encodings\\cp1252.py\", line 23, in decode\n File \"pickle.py\", line 1034, in load\n File \"pickle.py\", line 237, in read\nUnicodeDecodeError: 'charmap' codec can't decode byte 0x81 in position 51: character maps to <undefined>\n\nScript Executor Traceback:\nSystem.Text.DecoderFallbackException: character maps to <undefined>\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Runtime.LightExceptions.ThrowException(LightException lightEx)\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Runtime.LightExceptions.CheckAndThrow(Object value)\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Interpreter.FuncCallInstruction`2.Run(InterpretedFrame frame)\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Interpreter.Interpreter.HandleException(InterpretedFrame frame, Exception exception)\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Interpreter.Interpreter.Run(InterpretedFrame frame)\n at Microsoft.Scripting.Interpreter.LightLambda.Run2[T0,T1,TRet](T0 arg0, T1 arg1)\n at IronPython.Compiler.PythonScriptCode.RunWorker(CodeContext ctx)\n at PyRevitLabs.PyRevit.Runtime.IronPythonEngine.Execute(ScriptRuntime& runtime)\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\nSee above\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\n==> Installed Revits\n2024.1.1 (Update) | Version: 24.1.10.25 | Build: 20230830_0315(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2024\\\"\n Product: \"2024.1.1 (Update)\" | Engine: IPY342 (342) |\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "The tool was coded with ipy2712. You may want to use this engine and try to reproduce. @Wurschdhaud \nAlso, we need the full pyrevit env report to get the bare minimum context, you could use pyrevit 4.1 I wouldn't know.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "The tool was coded with ipy2712. You may want to use this engine and try to reproduce. @Wurschdhaud \nAlso, we need the full pyrevit env report to get the bare minimum context, you could use pyrevit 4.1 I wouldn't know.\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25149+1943-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15332029404)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25153+1459-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15395558670)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25154+0858-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15412944322)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25154+0920-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15413442991)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25155+0904-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15437610302)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+1125-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15583493178)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+1306-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15585617158)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+2030-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15594951406)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+0700-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15628454288)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1347-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15636046294)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1420-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15636716356)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1830-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15641415665)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25171+0757-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15774108075)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25181+1313-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15973807401)\n:package: New public release are available for [5.2.0.25181+1425](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases/tag/untagged-40ff17e053559dc898b3)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/62e5feaeca4401065ea6e07b2077277fd23af7d2"], "created_at": "2025-05-29T19:30:53Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2690, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2690", "issue_numbers": [2684], "base_commit": "ff1bdc7bb7e1e5d0275e2e373d4fd2ccb6acbbb5", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\nindex 4743d0e883..96687096e4 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\n@@ -137,10 +137,7 @@ def Execute(self, uiapp):\n                 ):\n                     # In case of rooms, spaces and areas. Check Color scheme is applied and if not\n                     if version > 2021:\n-                        if (\n-                            str(wndw.crt_view.GetColorFillSchemeId(sel_cat.cat.Id))\n-                            == \"-1\"\n-                        ):\n+                        if wndw.crt_view.GetColorFillSchemeId(sel_cat.cat.Id).ToString() is \"-1\":\n                             color_schemes = (\n                                 DB.FilteredElementCollector(new_doc)\n                                 .OfClass(DB.BuiltInCategoryFillScheme)\n@@ -1487,20 +1484,19 @@ def get_used_categories_parameters(cat_exc, acti_view):\n                 list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(0, par))\n         typ = ele.Document.GetElement(ele.GetTypeId())\n         # Type parameters\n-        if typ is None:\n-            continue\n-        for par in typ.Parameters:\n-            if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n-                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n-                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n-            ):\n-                list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n+        if typ:\n+            for par in typ.Parameters:\n+                if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n+                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n+                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n+                    ):\n+                    list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n         # Sort and add\n         list_parameters = sorted(\n-            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper(), reverse=False\n+        list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper()\n         )\n         list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n-    list_cat = sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name, reverse=False)\n+    list_cat = sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name)\n     return list_cat\n \n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]:  Latest version of Color Splasher detects less elements, including but not limited to MEP spaces and HVAC Zones..\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [ ] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [ ] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [ ] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [ ] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nI just installed the latest version of pyRevit (5.1.0.25094) to use the Color Splasher Save/Load Color Scheme for my MEP spaces and Zones and noticed it is detecting less elements. \n\nLatest version: 6 types detected\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a01b4103-472b-4aa3-a01e-947c60315ba0)\n\n\nOlder/previous version (v4.8.16.24121): 9 types detected\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4b5bc2cf-bc48-4d80-a8c2-0f8b4e594e11)\n\n\nBug or were these removed?\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nNo errors pop up. It is simply not detecting all the elements in the latest release.\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nMicrosoft Windows [Version 10.0.26100.4061]\n(c) Microsoft Corporation. All rights reserved.\n\nZ:\\>pyrevit env\n==> Registered Clones (full git repos)\n==> Registered Clones (deployed from archive/image)\nmaster | Branch: \"master\" | Version: \"5.1.0.25094+1131-wip\" | Path: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\n==> Attachments\nmaster | Product: \"2025 First Customer Ship\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\nmaster | Product: \"2023.1.6\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\nmaster | Product: \"2022.1.8\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\n==> Installed Extensions\nMEP Tools By RM | Type: Unknown | Repo: \"\" | Installed: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\OneDrive - HOK\\_My Hard Drive\\Python_Dynamo_C# Scripts\\MEP Tools By RM.extension\"\nMEP Tools By RM | Type: Unknown | Repo: \"\" | Installed: \"R:\\HOU\\DEPTS\\MEP\\_Mechanical Group\\PyRevit\\MEP Tools By RM.extension\"\nMEP Tools By RM v2 | Type: Unknown | Repo: \"\" | Installed: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\OneDrive - HOK\\_My Hard Drive\\My PyRevit\\MEP Tools By RM v2.extension\"\n==> Default Extension Search Path\nC:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit\\Extensions\n==> Extension Search Paths\nC:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\OneDrive - HOK\\_My Hard Drive\\Python_Dynamo_C# Scripts\nC:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\OneDrive - HOK\\_My Hard Drive\\My PyRevit\nR:\\HOU\\DEPTS\\MEP\\_Mechanical Group\\PyRevit\n==> Extension Sources - Default\nhttps://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/raw/master/extensions/extensions.json\n==> Extension Sources - Additional\n==> Installed Revits\n2025 First Customer Ship | Version: 25.0.2.419 | Build: 20240307_1300(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2025\\\"\n2023.1.6 | Version: 23.1.60.36 | Build: 20241107_1515(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2023\\\"\n2022.1.8 | Version: 22.1.80.32 | Build: 20241107_1515(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2022\\\"\n==> Running Revit Instances\n==> User Environment\nMicrosoft Windows 10 [Version 10.0.26100]\nExecuting User: GROUP\\rafael.martinez\nActive User:\nAdmin Access: No\n%APPDATA%: \"C:\\Users\\rafael.martinez\\AppData\\Roaming\"\nLatest Installed .Net Framework: 8.0.16\nNo .Net Target Packs are installed.\nNo .Net-Core Target Packs are installed.\npyRevit CLI v5.1.0.25094+1131-wip.ffa32944090b8fb19834361c5750674555b2c0a2\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "Can you replace the color fill of a Zone or Space manually by Element?\nin Revit 2026 (I  haven't tested earlier version):\n- you can only set visibility, transparency or halftone to a Space\n- for Zones, you supposidely can, but trying it out, it does not seem to affect the elements (zones)\nSince the color splasher only affects elements that can have graphics overrides, the spaces are not expected to show, but for the zones:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d32a155-2d83-4bfe-85d2-46dc7c8bee84)\nit shows but as the OG does not work in Revit on this cat, the color splasher cannot do its magic.\n\nThis might be a recent change in the API classes of the spaces and zones. But Revit 2026: No Go\nmanually yes. so i do have both versions of pyrevit installed and running them in the same session. I dug into, at least tried to, to see what could be a reason that it does not detect anymore and i see that in the latest version. i was able to get it see the spaces and zones by updating this part of the code from the latest version to what was in the v4.8.16.24121 version and that did the trick\n\ni simply changed this part:\n\n\"if typ is None:\" to \"if typ is not None:\", commented out \"continue\", and indented the for loop to match 4.8.16.24121\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/460914b5-da5d-4a81-b34c-371032f76dec)\n\nto this: (which is how the v4.8.16.24121 was formatted)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c29eeabb-52c2-4851-8a8a-1db1654ae2ef)\n\nsnippet from v4.8.16.24121\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f66d677b-4c36-4ad0-9a06-f25010dec329)\n\n\n\n\n@RalphMV1024 \nThe logic in this bloc is a bit of a mess, it should be split.\nLooking through quickly, this goes close to a solution: \n```\n        list_parameters = []\n        # Instance parameters\n        for par in ele.Parameters:\n            if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n            ):\n                list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(0, par))\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper(), reverse=False\n        )\n        typ = ele.Document.GetElement(ele.GetTypeId())\n        # Type parameters\n        if typ is None:\n            list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n            continue\n        for par in typ.Parameters:\n            if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n            ):\n                list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n        # Sort and add\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper(), reverse=False\n        )\n        list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n    return sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name, reverse=False)\n```\n\nbut there is still an error downstream with 'BuiltInCategoryFillScheme' applied to spaces\nyour right, i checked it out again and this worked now for both the zones and spaces. \n\n######### Type parameters - Updated part\n        if typ:\n            \n            for par in typ.Parameters:\n                if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n                ):\n                    list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n        # Sort and add\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper()\n            )\n        list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n    list_cat = sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name)\n    return list_cat\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Can you replace the color fill of a Zone or Space manually by Element?\nin Revit 2026 (I  haven't tested earlier version):\n- you can only set visibility, transparency or halftone to a Space\n- for Zones, you supposidely can, but trying it out, it does not seem to affect the elements (zones)\nSince the color splasher only affects elements that can have graphics overrides, the spaces are not expected to show, but for the zones:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d32a155-2d83-4bfe-85d2-46dc7c8bee84)\nit shows but as the OG does not work in Revit on this cat, the color splasher cannot do its magic.\n\nThis might be a recent change in the API classes of the spaces and zones. But Revit 2026: No Go\nmanually yes. so i do have both versions of pyrevit installed and running them in the same session. I dug into, at least tried to, to see what could be a reason that it does not detect anymore and i see that in the latest version. i was able to get it see the spaces and zones by updating this part of the code from the latest version to what was in the v4.8.16.24121 version and that did the trick\n\ni simply changed this part:\n\n\"if typ is None:\" to \"if typ is not None:\", commented out \"continue\", and indented the for loop to match 4.8.16.24121\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/460914b5-da5d-4a81-b34c-371032f76dec)\n\nto this: (which is how the v4.8.16.24121 was formatted)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c29eeabb-52c2-4851-8a8a-1db1654ae2ef)\n\nsnippet from v4.8.16.24121\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f66d677b-4c36-4ad0-9a06-f25010dec329)\n\n\n\n\n@RalphMV1024 \nThe logic in this bloc is a bit of a mess, it should be split.\nLooking through quickly, this goes close to a solution: \n```\n        list_parameters = []\n        # Instance parameters\n        for par in ele.Parameters:\n            if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n            ):\n                list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(0, par))\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper(), reverse=False\n        )\n        typ = ele.Document.GetElement(ele.GetTypeId())\n        # Type parameters\n        if typ is None:\n            list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n            continue\n        for par in typ.Parameters:\n            if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n            ):\n                list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n        # Sort and add\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper(), reverse=False\n        )\n        list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n    return sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name, reverse=False)\n```\n\nbut there is still an error downstream with 'BuiltInCategoryFillScheme' applied to spaces\nyour right, i checked it out again and this worked now for both the zones and spaces. \n\n######### Type parameters - Updated part\n        if typ:\n            \n            for par in typ.Parameters:\n                if par.Definition.BuiltInParameter not in (\n                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM,\n                    DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_CATEGORY_PARAM_MT,\n                ):\n                    list_parameters.append(ParameterInfo(1, par))\n        # Sort and add\n        list_parameters = sorted(\n            list_parameters, key=lambda x: x.name.upper()\n            )\n        list_cat.append(CategoryInfo(ele.Category, list_parameters))\n    list_cat = sorted(list_cat, key=lambda x: x.name)\n    return list_cat\nThanks @RalphMV1024 \nGood pointer.\nI also fixed the broken behaviour down the line with `BuiltInCategoryFillScheme`\n\n#2690 fixes it, you can try it with the latest WIP in a bit\n#2691 does fix it properly, I was too prompt on my PR validation ;p\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/e70f885af0044019dd61b7a2e7f5252917a57d27"], "created_at": "2025-06-03T08:54:12Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2693, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2693", "issue_numbers": [2692], "base_commit": "a743245d0c939cc0462a9d988431823c3e319d0c", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/forms/SelectFromList.xaml b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/forms/SelectFromList.xaml\nindex 8ab837a075..508fb273d1 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/forms/SelectFromList.xaml\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/forms/SelectFromList.xaml\n@@ -132,7 +132,7 @@\n                       ItemTemplate=\"{DynamicResource ItemContainerTemplate}\"\n                       ItemsPanel=\"{DynamicResource ItemsPanelTemplate}\"\n                       VirtualizingStackPanel.IsVirtualizing=\"True\"\n-                      VirtualizingStackPanel.VirtualizationMode=\"Recycling\"\n+                      VirtualizingStackPanel.VirtualizationMode=\"Standard\"\n                       ScrollViewer.CanContentScroll=\"True\"/>\n             <GridSplitter x:Name=\"infoSplitter\" Grid.Column=\"1\" VerticalAlignment=\"Stretch\"  HorizontalAlignment=\"Stretch\" ResizeDirection=\"Columns\" Visibility=\"Collapsed\" />\n             <ScrollViewer x:Name=\"infoPanel\" Grid.Column=\"2\" Visibility=\"Collapsed\">\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Set Revisions to Sheets - Sheets unchecked when scrolling\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nAs in the gif below, I selected 2 sheets then I scroll the list up and down, the 1st sheet is deselected.\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25d476ac-b347-42b0-8762-cea0aa4e7266)\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nAs mentioned above\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n1. Run Set revision to sheet\n2. Select any revision\n3. Select first 2 sheets\n4. Scroll up and down using the scroll wheel\n5. Notices the 1st sheet is deselected\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\n==> Registered Clones (full git repos)\n==> Registered Clones (deployed from archive/image)\n==> Attachments\nUnknown | Product: \"2025 First Customer Ship\" | Manifest: \"C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\Revit\\Addins\\2025\\pyRevit.addin\"\nUnknown | Product: \"2024.3.1\" | Manifest: \"C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\Revit\\Addins\\2024\\pyRevit.addin\"\nUnknown | Product: \"Autodesk Revit 2023\" | Manifest: \"C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\Revit\\Addins\\2023\\pyRevit.addin\"\nUnknown | Product: \"Autodesk Revit 2022\" | Manifest: \"C:\\ProgramData\\Autodesk\\Revit\\Addins\\2022\\pyRevit.addin\"\n==> Installed Extensions\n==> Default Extension Search Path\nC:\\Users\\xxx\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit\\Extensions\n==> Extension Search Paths\n==> Extension Sources - Default\nhttps://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/raw/master/extensions/extensions.json\n==> Extension Sources - Additional\n==> Installed Revits\n2025 First Customer Ship | Version: 25.0.2.419 | Build: 20240307_1300(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2025\\\"\n2024.3.1 | Version: 24.3.10.22 | Build: 20241105_1515(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2024\\\"\nAutodesk Revit 2023 | Version: 23.1.60.36 | Build: 20241107_1515(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2023\\\"\nAutodesk Revit 2022 | Version: 22.1.80.32 | Build: 20241107_1515(x64) | Language: 1033 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2022\\\"\n==> Running Revit Instances\nError: Object reference not set to an instance of an object.\nRun with \"--debug\" option to see debug messages\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "I cannot reproduce.\nWhat version of pyRevit are you using?\n\n> I cannot reproduce. What version of pyRevit are you using?\n\nPyrevit CLI 5.0.1.25051\nCan you provide a minimal Revit file with which you can reproduce + list of other plugins installed + Revit version being used for this bug?\n> Can you provide a minimal Revit file with which you can reproduce + list of other plugins installed + Revit version being used for this bug?\n\nI tried it on Revit 23 and 25 on a few projects, even the Revit Sample file one, I only have Ideate addin turned on now.\nI think to recreate it exactly, you will need to highlight the sheet first, then scroll up and down, as you can see in the gif, after I scroll, the checkbox is back to checked without clicking.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f4b2c56f-0154-4344-b5da-eae3e198273e)\nThere you go.\nI managed to reproduce. This is a real bug. \ud83d\ude04 \n\nThe state management is improperly implemented. When the item unchecked becomes out of focus when scrolling down, it does not remember its new state, so that when scrolling back up, it comes back to its checked state.\nbug introduced:\nhttps://github.com/jmcouffin/pyRevit/commit/f370edeeef9231828041298ac7227567a1c7ce09#diff-b655b2965d511e3cd2fa97e441c9876a7bb25d8d8be6d1d0244887adaaa49ccdR135\n\nSetting `Recycling` to `Standard` should do the trick with a reasonable performance hit.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I cannot reproduce.\nWhat version of pyRevit are you using?\n\n> I cannot reproduce. What version of pyRevit are you using?\n\nPyrevit CLI 5.0.1.25051\nCan you provide a minimal Revit file with which you can reproduce + list of other plugins installed + Revit version being used for this bug?\n> Can you provide a minimal Revit file with which you can reproduce + list of other plugins installed + Revit version being used for this bug?\n\nI tried it on Revit 23 and 25 on a few projects, even the Revit Sample file one, I only have Ideate addin turned on now.\nI think to recreate it exactly, you will need to highlight the sheet first, then scroll up and down, as you can see in the gif, after I scroll, the checkbox is back to checked without clicking.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f4b2c56f-0154-4344-b5da-eae3e198273e)\nThere you go.\nI managed to reproduce. This is a real bug. \ud83d\ude04 \n\nThe state management is improperly implemented. When the item unchecked becomes out of focus when scrolling down, it does not remember its new state, so that when scrolling back up, it comes back to its checked state.\nbug introduced:\nhttps://github.com/jmcouffin/pyRevit/commit/f370edeeef9231828041298ac7227567a1c7ce09#diff-b655b2965d511e3cd2fa97e441c9876a7bb25d8d8be6d1d0244887adaaa49ccdR135\n\nSetting `Recycling` to `Standard` should do the trick with a reasonable performance hit.\nfixed by #2693 \n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25155+0904-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15437610302)\n> There you go. I managed to reproduce. This is a real bug. \ud83d\ude04\n\nhahaha figured it out by accident, thanks for the prompt responses.\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+1125-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15583493178)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+1306-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15585617158)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25162+2030-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15594951406)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+0700-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15628454288)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1347-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15636046294)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1420-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15636716356)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25164+1830-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15641415665)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.1.0.25171+0757-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15774108075)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25181+1313-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/15973807401)\n:package: New public release are available for [5.2.0.25181+1425](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases/tag/untagged-40ff17e053559dc898b3)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/7b479190758964dc789a61e1e63cd4584aca97b0"], "created_at": "2025-06-04T08:31:47Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2737, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2737", "issue_numbers": [2695], "base_commit": "110928e31a31da7d96226e9e83f885d32c1d553b", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/Test Project Parameters.pushbutton/script.py b/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/Test Project Parameters.pushbutton/script.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..d16e0917f0\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/Test Project Parameters.pushbutton/script.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,332 @@\n+# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-\n+\"\"\"Test Project Parameters Functions - Issue #2695\"\"\"\n+\n+__context__ = \"zero-doc\"\n+\n+import sys\n+import traceback\n+import time\n+from pyrevit import script\n+from pyrevit.revit.db.query import (\n+    get_project_parameters,\n+    iter_project_parameters,\n+    model_has_parameter,\n+)\n+\n+# Get the output window\n+output = script.get_output()\n+\n+\n+def test_debug_imports():\n+    \"\"\"Debug test to isolate import issues\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Debug: Testing imports...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+        output.print_md(\"   Checking get_project_parameters...\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   [PASS] get_project_parameters available\")\n+\n+        output.print_md(\"   Checking iter_project_parameters...\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   [PASS] iter_project_parameters available\")\n+\n+        output.print_md(\"   Checking model_has_parameter...\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   [PASS] model_has_parameter available\")\n+\n+        output.print_md(\"   Testing get_project_parameters() call...\")\n+        result = get_project_parameters()\n+        output.print_md(\"   [PASS] get_project_parameters() executed successfully\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   Found {} parameters\".format(len(result)))\n+\n+        return True\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def test_basic_functionality():\n+    \"\"\"Test that iterator produces same results as original function\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Testing basic functionality...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+\n+        # Get results both ways\n+        original_list = get_project_parameters()\n+        iterator_list = list(iter_project_parameters())\n+\n+        output.print_md(\n+            \"   Original function: **{}** parameters\".format(len(original_list))\n+        )\n+        output.print_md(\n+            \"   Iterator function: **{}** parameters\".format(len(iterator_list))\n+        )\n+\n+        # Compare counts\n+        if len(original_list) == len(iterator_list):\n+            output.print_md(\"   [PASS] Parameter counts match\")\n+        else:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [FAIL] Parameter counts don't match!\")\n+            return False\n+\n+        # Compare first few parameters if they exist\n+        if original_list and iterator_list:\n+            for i, (orig, iter_param) in enumerate(\n+                zip(original_list[:3], iterator_list[:3])\n+            ):\n+                if orig.name == iter_param.name:\n+                    output.print_md(\n+                        \"   [PASS] Parameter {} '{}' matches\".format(i + 1, orig.name)\n+                    )\n+                else:\n+                    output.print_md(\n+                        \"   [FAIL] Parameter {} mismatch: '{}' vs '{}'\".format(\n+                            i + 1, orig.name, iter_param.name\n+                        )\n+                    )\n+                    return False\n+\n+        return True\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def test_early_termination():\n+    \"\"\"Test that iterator can terminate early\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Testing early termination...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+\n+        # Test early termination - get only first 3 parameters\n+        count = 0\n+        first_five = []\n+        for param in iter_project_parameters():\n+            first_five.append(param)\n+            count += 1\n+            if count >= 5:\n+                break\n+\n+        total_params = len(get_project_parameters())\n+\n+        output.print_md(\"   Retrieved first **{}** parameters\".format(len(first_five)))\n+        output.print_md(\"   Total available: **{}** parameters\".format(total_params))\n+\n+        # List the parameters that were retrieved\n+        if first_five:\n+            output.print_md(\"   Parameters retrieved:\")\n+            for i, param in enumerate(first_five, 1):\n+                output.print_md(\"     {}. {}\".format(i, param.name))\n+\n+        if len(first_five) == 5 and total_params >= 5:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [PASS] Early termination works correctly\")\n+            return True\n+        elif total_params < 5:\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   [PASS] Early termination works (only {} parameters available)\".format(\n+                    total_params\n+                )\n+            )\n+            return True\n+        else:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [FAIL] Early termination failed\")\n+            return False\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def test_boolean_return():\n+    \"\"\"Test that model_has_parameter returns proper boolean\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Testing boolean return...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+\n+        # Get a real parameter name if available\n+        params = get_project_parameters()\n+        if params:\n+            real_param_name = params[0].name\n+            result_real = model_has_parameter(real_param_name)\n+\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   Testing with real parameter: '{}'\".format(real_param_name)\n+            )\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   Result: **{}** (type: {})\".format(\n+                    result_real, type(result_real).__name__\n+                )\n+            )\n+\n+            if isinstance(result_real, bool) and result_real:\n+                output.print_md(\"   [PASS] Returns True for existing parameter\")\n+            else:\n+                output.print_md(\"   [FAIL] Should return True for existing parameter\")\n+                return False\n+\n+        # Test with fake parameter\n+        fake_result = model_has_parameter(\"NonExistentParameter12345\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   Testing with fake parameter: 'NonExistentParameter12345'\")\n+        output.print_md(\n+            \"   Result: **{}** (type: {})\".format(\n+                fake_result, type(fake_result).__name__\n+            )\n+        )\n+\n+        if isinstance(fake_result, bool) and not fake_result:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [PASS] Returns False for non-existent parameter\")\n+            return True\n+        else:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [FAIL] Should return False for non-existent parameter\")\n+            return False\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def _get_project_parameters_original(doc=None):\n+    \"\"\"Original implementation for performance comparison\"\"\"\n+    from pyrevit.revit.db.query import get_defined_sharedparams\n+    from pyrevit import DOCS\n+    from pyrevit.revit import db\n+\n+    doc = doc or DOCS.doc\n+    shared_params = {x.Name: x for x in get_defined_sharedparams()}\n+\n+    pp_list = []\n+    if doc and not doc.IsFamilyDocument:\n+        param_bindings = doc.ParameterBindings\n+        pb_iterator = param_bindings.ForwardIterator()\n+        pb_iterator.Reset()\n+        while pb_iterator.MoveNext():\n+            msp = db.ProjectParameter(\n+                pb_iterator.Key,\n+                param_bindings[pb_iterator.Key],\n+                param_ext_def=shared_params.get(pb_iterator.Key.Name, None),\n+            )\n+            pp_list.append(msp)\n+    return pp_list\n+\n+\n+def test_performance():\n+    \"\"\"Performance comparison between original and iterator implementations\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Testing performance...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+\n+        # Time original implementation\n+        start_time = time.time()\n+        original_result = _get_project_parameters_original()\n+        original_time = time.time() - start_time\n+\n+        # Time new implementation (via get_project_parameters)\n+        start_time = time.time()\n+        new_result = get_project_parameters()\n+        new_time = time.time() - start_time\n+\n+        output.print_md(\n+            \"   Original implementation: **{:.4f}s** ({} parameters)\".format(\n+                original_time, len(original_result)\n+            )\n+        )\n+        output.print_md(\n+            \"   New implementation: **{:.4f}s** ({} parameters)\".format(\n+                new_time, len(new_result)\n+            )\n+        )\n+\n+        # Compare new implementation to original\n+        if new_time <= original_time * 1.1:  # Allow 10% tolerance\n+            output.print_md(\"   [PASS] New implementation performance is acceptable\")\n+        else:\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   [INFO] New implementation is slower (but provides iterator benefits)\"\n+            )\n+\n+        # Verify both implementations return same count\n+        if len(original_result) == len(new_result):\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   [PASS] Both implementations return same parameter count\"\n+            )\n+        else:\n+            output.print_md(\n+                \"   [FAIL] Parameter counts don't match between implementations\"\n+            )\n+\n+        return True\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def test_list_parameters():\n+    \"\"\"List all parameter names\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"## Listing all project parameters...\")\n+\n+    try:\n+        # Get all parameters\n+        params = get_project_parameters()\n+\n+        if not params:\n+            output.print_md(\"   [INFO] No project parameters found in current document\")\n+            return True\n+\n+        output.print_md(\"   Found **{}** project parameters:\".format(len(params)))\n+        output.print_md(\"   | # | Parameter Name |\")\n+        output.print_md(\"   |---|---------------|\")\n+\n+        # List all parameters\n+        for i, param in enumerate(params, 1):\n+            output.print_md(\"   | {} | {} |\".format(i, param.name))\n+\n+        return True\n+\n+    except Exception as e:\n+        output.print_md(\"   [ERROR] Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+        traceback.print_exc()\n+        return False\n+\n+\n+def run_all_tests():\n+    \"\"\"Run all tests\"\"\"\n+    output.print_md(\"# Project Parameters Tests - Issue #2695\")\n+    output.print_md(\"---\")\n+\n+    tests = [\n+        (\"Debug Imports\", test_debug_imports),\n+        (\"List Parameters\", test_list_parameters),\n+        (\"Basic Functionality\", test_basic_functionality),\n+        (\"Early Termination\", test_early_termination),\n+        (\"Boolean Return on model_has_parameter\", test_boolean_return),\n+        (\"Performance\", test_performance),\n+    ]\n+\n+    passed = 0\n+    total = len(tests)\n+\n+    for test_name, test_func in tests:\n+        try:\n+            if test_func():\n+                passed += 1\n+        except Exception as e:\n+            output.print_md(\"## [CRASHED] {}\".format(test_name))\n+            output.print_md(\"Error: {}\".format(str(e)))\n+            traceback.print_exc()\n+\n+    output.print_md(\"---\")\n+    output.print_md(\"# Results: **{}/{}** tests passed\".format(passed, total))\n+\n+    if passed == total:\n+        output.print_md(\"## All tests passed!\")\n+    else:\n+        output.print_md(\"## {} test(s) failed\".format(total - passed))\n+\n+\n+if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+    run_all_tests()\ndiff --git a/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/bundle.yaml b/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/bundle.yaml\nindex 83de167b8d..3e8678d1f4 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/bundle.yaml\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitDevTools.extension/pyRevitDev.tab/Debug.panel/Unit Tests.pulldown/bundle.yaml\n@@ -27,3 +27,5 @@ layout:\n   - Test Toast\n   - Test FillPatternViewer\n   - Test Family API\n+  - -----\n+  - Test Project Parameters\ndiff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/query.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/query.py\nindex cf29990fa8..c942bab317 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/query.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/query.py\n@@ -734,15 +734,15 @@ def get_critical_warnings_count(warnings, critical_warnings_template):\n     Counts the number of critical warnings from a list of warnings based on a template.\n \n     Args:\n-        warnings (list): A list of warning objects. Each warning object should have a method \n+        warnings (list): A list of warning objects. Each warning object should have a method\n                          `GetFailureDefinitionId` that returns an object with a `Guid` attribute.\n-        critical_warnings_template (list): A list of string representations of GUIDs that are \n+        critical_warnings_template (list): A list of string representations of GUIDs that are\n                                            considered critical warnings.\n \n     Returns:\n         int: The count of critical warnings.\n     \"\"\"\n-    warnings_guid = [warning.GetFailureDefinitionId().Guid for warning in warnings] \n+    warnings_guid = [warning.GetFailureDefinitionId().Guid for warning in warnings]\n     return sum(\n         1\n         for warning_guid in warnings_guid\n@@ -789,33 +789,58 @@ def get_defined_sharedparams():\n     return pp_list\n \n \n-def get_project_parameters(doc=None):\n+def iter_project_parameters(doc=None):\n     \"\"\"\n-    Retrieves the project parameters from the given Revit document.\n+    Generator that yields project parameters from the given Revit document one at a time.\n \n     Args:\n         doc (Document, optional): The Revit document from which to retrieve the project parameters.\n                                   If not provided, defaults to `DOCS.doc`.\n \n-    Returns:\n-        list: A list of ProjectParameter objects representing the project parameters in the document.\n+    Yields:\n+        ProjectParameter: Individual ProjectParameter objects representing the project parameters in the document.\n     \"\"\"\n     doc = doc or DOCS.doc\n-    shared_params = {x.Name: x for x in get_defined_sharedparams()}\n \n-    pp_list = []\n+    # Build shared params dictionary more explicitly to avoid IronPython issues\n+    shared_params = {}\n+    try:\n+        defined_shared_params = get_defined_sharedparams()\n+        for param in defined_shared_params:\n+            shared_params[param.Name] = param\n+    except Exception:\n+        # If shared params can't be loaded, continue with empty dict\n+        pass\n+\n     if doc and not doc.IsFamilyDocument:\n         param_bindings = doc.ParameterBindings\n         pb_iterator = param_bindings.ForwardIterator()\n         pb_iterator.Reset()\n         while pb_iterator.MoveNext():\n+            key = pb_iterator.Key\n+            binding = param_bindings[key]\n+            param_ext_def = shared_params.get(key.Name, None)\n+\n             msp = db.ProjectParameter(\n-                pb_iterator.Key,\n-                param_bindings[pb_iterator.Key],\n-                param_ext_def=shared_params.get(pb_iterator.Key.Name, None),\n+                key,\n+                binding,\n+                param_ext_def=param_ext_def,\n             )\n-            pp_list.append(msp)\n-    return pp_list\n+            yield msp\n+\n+\n+def get_project_parameters(doc=None):\n+    \"\"\"\n+    Retrieves the project parameters from the given Revit document.\n+\n+    Args:\n+        doc (Document, optional): The Revit document from which to retrieve the project parameters.\n+                                  If not provided, defaults to `DOCS.doc`.\n+\n+    Returns:\n+        list: A list of ProjectParameter objects representing the project parameters in the document.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    return list(iter_project_parameters(doc))\n \n \n def get_project_parameter_id(param_name, doc=None):\n@@ -834,7 +859,7 @@ def get_project_parameter_id(param_name, doc=None):\n         PyRevitException: If the parameter with the specified name is not found.\n     \"\"\"\n     doc = doc or DOCS.doc\n-    for project_param in get_project_parameters(doc):\n+    for project_param in iter_project_parameters(doc):\n         if project_param.name == param_name:\n             return project_param.param_id\n     raise PyRevitException(\"Parameter not found: {}\".format(param_name))\n@@ -851,8 +876,7 @@ def get_project_parameter(param_id_or_name, doc=None):\n     Returns:\n         ProjectParameter: The matching project parameter if found, otherwise None.\n     \"\"\"\n-    pp_list = get_project_parameters(doc or DOCS.doc)\n-    for msp in pp_list:\n+    for msp in iter_project_parameters(doc or DOCS.doc):\n         if msp == param_id_or_name:\n             return msp\n     return None\n@@ -869,7 +893,7 @@ def model_has_parameter(param_id_or_name, doc=None):\n     Returns:\n         bool: True if the parameter exists in the model, False otherwise.\n     \"\"\"\n-    return get_project_parameter(param_id_or_name, doc=doc)\n+    return get_project_parameter(param_id_or_name, doc=doc) is not None\n \n \n def get_global_parameters(doc=None):\n@@ -1171,10 +1195,10 @@ def get_rvt_link_status(doc=None):\n def get_rvt_link_doc_name(rvtlink_instance):\n     \"\"\"\n     Retrieves the name of the Revit link document from the given Revit link instance.\n-    \n+\n     Args:\n         rvtlink_instance: The Revit link instance from which to extract the document name.\n-    \n+\n     Returns:\n         str: The name of the Revit link document, without the file extension and any directory paths.\n     \"\"\"\n@@ -1184,10 +1208,10 @@ def get_rvt_link_doc_name(rvtlink_instance):\n def get_rvt_link_instance_name(rvtlink_instance=None):\n     \"\"\"\n     Retrieves the name of a Revit link instance.\n-    \n+\n     Args:\n         rvtlink_instance: The Revit link instance object.\n-    \n+\n     Returns:\n         str: The name of the Revit link instance, extracted from the full name.\n     \"\"\"\n@@ -1490,11 +1514,11 @@ def get_schedules_on_sheet(viewsheet, doc=None):\n def get_schedules_instances(doc=None):\n     \"\"\"\n     Retrieves all schedule instances placed on sheets.\n-    \n+\n     Args:\n-        doc (Document, optional): The Revit document to search within. If not provided, \n+        doc (Document, optional): The Revit document to search within. If not provided,\n                                   the default document (DOCS.doc) will be used.\n-    \n+\n     Returns:\n         List[ScheduleSheetInstance]: A list of ScheduleSheetInstance elements.\n     \"\"\"\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "add a `iter_project_parameters` to make the related functions more efficient\n## Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe\n\n`get_project_paramters` returns a list of parameters, but the functions below that uses it only need an iterator to get the requested item.\n\nhttps://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/blob/develop/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/query.py#L792-L858\n\n\n## Describe the solution you'd like\n\n- add a `iter_project_parameters` function with the content of the current `get_project_parameters` but with `yield` instead of the list generation\n- transform the `get_project_partameters` to `return list(iter_project_parameters)`\n- use `iter_project_parameters` in the functions below\n\nAlso, `model_has_parameter` doesn't really return a boolean, we should add a `is not None` at the end of the return line.\n\n## Additional context\n\nThere might be other situations like this in the code, no need to waste memory with lists to only get one (or some) item!\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": ":package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25211+1247-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16622867577)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25213+1402-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16676983706)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25216+1027-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16720557337)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25216+1429-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16725919288)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25219+0909-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16800064120)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25219+1354-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16806444749)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25219+1400-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16806592632)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25219+1405-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16806685204)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25219+1421-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/16807098303