eWelcomePage=no\n WizardStyle=classic\n WizardImageFile=.\\pyrevit-cli.bmp\n WizardSmallImageFile=.\\pyrevit-banner.bmp\n+ArchitecturesInstallIn64BitMode=x64\n \n [Languages]\n Name: \"english\"; MessagesFile: \"compiler:Default.isl\"\n@@ -60,4 +61,12 @@ Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; Description: \"Detach existing clones...\"; Par\n \n [UninstallRun]\n Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"ClearCaches\"; Parameters: \"caches clear --all\"; Flags: runhidden runascurrentuser\n-Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"DetachClones\"; Parameters: \"detach --all\"; Flags: runhidden runascurrentuser\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"DetachClones\"; Parameters: \"detach --all\"; Flags: runhidden runascurrentuser\n+\n+[Code]\n+function InitializeSetup: Boolean;\n+begin\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80;\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80Desktop;\n+  Result := True;\n+end;\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/release/pyrevit-cli.iss b/release/pyrevit-cli.iss\nindex cdbddaeaaa..53f849b5b6 100644\n--- a/release/pyrevit-cli.iss\n+++ b/release/pyrevit-cli.iss\n@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@\n #define MyAppPublisher \"pyRevitLabs\"\n #define MyAppURL \"pyrevitlabs.io\"\n #define MyAppExeName \"pyrevit.exe\"\n+#include \"CodeDependencies.iss\"\n \n [Setup]\n ; App information\n@@ -21,7 +22,6 @@ DefaultGroupName={#MyAppName}\n DisableDirPage=auto\n DisableStartupPrompt=yes\n DisableProgramGroupPage=yes\n-ArchitecturesInstallIn64BitMode=x64\n ChangesEnvironment=yes\n ;     path\n DefaultDirName={autopf}\\{#MyAppName}\n@@ -39,6 +39,7 @@ DisableWelcomePage=no\n WizardStyle=classic\n WizardImageFile=.\\pyrevit-cli.bmp\n WizardSmallImageFile=.\\pyrevit-banner.bmp\n+ArchitecturesInstallIn64BitMode=x64\n \n [Languages]\n Name: \"english\"; MessagesFile: \"compiler:Default.isl\"\n@@ -60,4 +61,12 @@ Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; Description: \"Detach existing clones...\"; Par\n \n [UninstallRun]\n Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"ClearCaches\"; Parameters: \"caches clear --all\"; Flags: runhidden\n-Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"DetachClones\"; Parameters: \"detach --all\"; Flags: runhidden\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"DetachClones\"; Parameters: \"detach --all\"; Flags: runhidden\n+\n+[Code]\n+function InitializeSetup: Boolean;\n+begin\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80;\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80Desktop;\n+  Result := True;\n+end;\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/release/pyrevit.iss b/release/pyrevit.iss\nindex 1048dfa6f8..2a6c8e5682 100644\n--- a/release/pyrevit.iss\n+++ b/release/pyrevit.iss\n@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@\n #define MyAppVersion \"5.2.0.25181\"\n #define MyAppPublisher \"pyRevitLabs\"\n #define MyAppURL \"pyrevitlabs.io\"\n+#include \"CodeDependencies.iss\"\n \n [Setup]\n ; App information\n@@ -20,7 +21,6 @@ DefaultGroupName={#MyAppName}\n DisableDirPage=auto\n DisableStartupPrompt=yes\n DisableProgramGroupPage=yes\n-ArchitecturesInstallIn64BitMode=x64\n ChangesEnvironment=yes\n ;     path\n DefaultDirName={userappdata}\\{#MyAppName}-Master\n@@ -38,6 +38,7 @@ DisableWelcomePage=no\n WizardStyle=classic\n WizardImageFile=.\\pyrevit.bmp\n WizardSmallImageFile=.\\pyrevit-banner.bmp\n+ArchitecturesInstallIn64BitMode=x64\n \n [Languages]\n Name: \"english\"; MessagesFile: \"compiler:Default.isl\"\n@@ -85,3 +86,11 @@ Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; Description: \"Attaching this clone...\"; Param\n [UninstallRun]\n Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"ClearCaches\"; Parameters: \"caches clear --all\"; Flags: runhidden\n Filename: \"{app}\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\"; RunOnceId: \"DetachClones\"; Parameters: \"detach --all\"; Flags: runhidden\n+\n+[Code]\n+function InitializeSetup: Boolean;\n+begin\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80;\n+  Dependency_AddDotNet80Desktop;\n+  Result := True;\n+end;\n\\ No newline at end of file\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Installer does not check for .NET \"core\" runtime\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nAfter installing pyRevit it does not show up in the Revit toolbar and does not prompt to load when opening revit for the first time after installation.\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nNothing\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n1. Install the latest version (5.2.0.25181 at the moment)\n2. Launch Revit to check the plugin\n3. Do not see the window asking about loading the plugin\n4. Search for a solution to the problem\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\nI expected the plugin to start\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nC:\\Windows\\system32>pyrevit env\nYou must install .NET to run this application.\n\nApp: C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\\bin\\pyrevit.exe\nArchitecture: x64\nApp host version: 8.0.17\n.NET location: Not found\n\nLearn more:\nhttps://aka.ms/dotnet/app-launch-failed\n\nDownload the .NET runtime:\nhttps://aka.ms/dotnet-core-applaunch?missing_runtime=true&arch=x64&rid=win-x64&os=win10&apphost_version=8.0.17\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\nOC: Windows Server 2022 21H2 20348.2849\n\n**My problem is SOLVED, solution below!**\n_\n\n> I don't speak English very well and this text was written using Google Translate,\nI apologize in advance for any inaccuracies or misunderstandings.\n\n_\nHello to the developers and other applicants for this problem.\nI am an IT specialist, with some knowledge of githab and how to search for errors in certain problems. I hope that this ticket will help someone in the future quickly fix the same problem as me.\n\n**_SOLUTION:_**\nAs you can see above, when I ran the `pyrevit env` command in cmd as administrator, it told me that I do not have .NET application installed. I solved it like this:\n1. Removed all installed versions of pyRevit\n2. Downloaded the latest version of .NET from the official Microsoft website:\nhttps://dotnet.microsoft.com/en-us/download/dotnet/8.0\n3. Reinstalled pyRevit, version Admin / All Users\nAfter that, I ran `pyrevit env` and this is what I got:\n<img width=\"1058\" height=\"566\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/86514bd5-6e21-44b7-85ba-37876783bce1\" />\n\n\nInitially, I thought that this plugin in principle does not work well with Windows Server, but after installing it on another server, everything worked out the first time and everything works fine\n(as far as I can judge by the work in principle, but not its correct operation, I do not know from the designer's side how it should work):\n_cmd_ => `pyrevit env` from another server:\n\n<img width=\"1116\" height=\"612\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8406a2db-7cb9-4dfc-a858-7acd2fc175d7\" />\n\nThen, I started looking for similar problems in GitHub and on the forum and did not find anything similar. Therefore, I began to figure out how my servers are different.\nI guess I just needed to update .NET Framework, not .NET, but now everything works, and as they say: \"If it works, don't touch it\".\n\nI hope this solution helps someone in the future!\n", "hints_text": "Hi @Maxumer72, thanks for the detailed bug report and the solution!\n\nThis is a problem with the pyrevit cli from version 5, that has been compiled against .NET ~~6~~ **8** like the pyrevit addin for Revit 2025 (and now 2026), so it needs that runtime, even though you don't have Revit 2025+ installed.\n\nThe installer calls the pyrevit cli to attach pyrevit to the various revit versions, but it doesn't give any message if there's been an error.\n\nWe should definitely add a check for the presence of the .net runtime in the installer, or bubble up the error with a user friendly message.\nI'm glad to help develop your product)\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi @Maxumer72, thanks for the detailed bug report and the solution!\n\nThis is a problem with the pyrevit cli from version 5, that has been compiled against .NET ~~6~~ **8** like the pyrevit addin for Revit 2025 (and now 2026), so it needs that runtime, even though you don't have Revit 2025+ installed.\n\nThe installer calls the pyrevit cli to attach pyrevit to the various revit versions, but it doesn't give any message if there's been an error.\n\nWe should definitely add a check for the presence of the .net runtime in the installer, or bubble up the error with a user friendly message.\nI'm glad to help develop your product)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/cde35b086990015ac1a76c2d0128e54a3432e915", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/2df1d37b01fee4b8d54d3c831d51a45be3c632c2", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/0727610544edcc0aa1c9c4d368036e08bc442f31", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/a5e935b00a770e09fddfa0a4e6b754fa426a7612", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/024be2603bbb74b3fb6c606d2055b53cfc81c833", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/af3723879a897a925bdb32bffbdc3fe8dd42799b", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/830005ec7dbecbb1f3779c9d0e005ad5cc0190a2", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/379e789e8f45aa30ac1918f0a8772d6431f81522"], "created_at": "2025-08-19T19:48:54Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2802, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2802", "issue_numbers": [2799], "base_commit": "ffb908a028baf068aed40ba03b1ba9f38e9774b0", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/__init__.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/__init__.py\nindex 2c1bb77dfc..7ad95cc0f1 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/__init__.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/__init__.py\n@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@\n from collections import namedtuple\n import traceback\n import re\n+from pyrevit.compat import PY3\n \n import clr  # pylint: disable=E0401\n \n@@ -31,8 +32,12 @@\n \n # extract version from version file\n VERSION_STRING = '0.0.'\n-with open(op.join(op.dirname(__file__), 'version'), 'r') as version_file:\n-    VERSION_STRING = version_file.read()\n+if PY3:\n+    with open(op.join(op.dirname(__file__), 'version'), 'r', encoding='utf-8') as version_file:\n+        VERSION_STRING = version_file.read()\n+else:\n+    with open(op.join(op.dirname(__file__), 'version'), 'r') as version_file:\n+        VERSION_STRING = version_file.read()\n matches = re.findall(r'(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)\\.?(.+)?', VERSION_STRING)[0]\n if len(matches) == 4:\n     VERSION_MAJOR, VERSION_MINOR, VERSION_PATCH, BUILD_METADATA = matches\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: unknown encoding: cp936 on Chinese Windows due to version-dependent open() behavior\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\npyRevit fails to load on systems where the default locale is set to Chinese (Simplified, PRC). The loading process is interrupted by a LookupError: unknown encoding: cp936 traceback.\n\nThe error originates from the core __init__.py file within pyrevitlib/pyrevit. The code attempts to open the version file in text mode ('r') without specifying an encoding. On a Chinese Windows system, the open() function defaults to the system's codepage, which is cp9 acidente (also known as GBK). The IronPython 3.4 environment used by pyRevit is unable to resolve this encoding, leading to the crash.\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nIronPython Traceback:\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\\bin\\netfx\\engines\\pyRevitLoader.py\", line 30, in <module>\n  File \"<string>\", line 540, in _check_name_wrapper\n  File \"<string>\", line 1188, in _load_unlocked\n  File \"<string>\", line 1117, in _exec\n  File \"<string>\", line 1459, in exec_module\n  File \"<string>\", line 1565, in load_module\n  File \"<string>\", line 597, in load_module_shim\n  File \"<string>\", line 1208, in load\n  File \"<string>\", line 322, in _call_with_frames_removed\n  File \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\\pyrevitlib\\pyrevit\\__init__.py\", line 35, in <module>\nLookupError: unknown encoding: cp936\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\n==> Registered Clones (full git repos)\n==> Registered Clones (deployed from archive/image)\nmaster | Branch: \"master\" | Version: \"5.2.0.25181+1332\" | Path: \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\n==> Attachments\nmaster | Product: \"2026 First Customer Ship\" | Engine: IPY342 (342) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\nmaster | Product: \"2025 First Customer Ship\" | Engine: IPY342 (342) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\nmaster | Product: \"Autodesk Revit 2023\" | Engine: IPY342 (342) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\nmaster | Product: \"2022.1.8\" | Engine: IPY342 (342) | Path: \"C:\\Users\\zhang\\AppData\\Roaming\\pyRevit-Master\"\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\nThe problem arises from the differing behavior of the open() function across Python 2 and Python 3, specifically concerning the explicit encoding parameter. To ensure compatibility and resolve the encoding issue, a conditional approach based on the Python version is required.\n\nFile to modify: pyrevitlib/pyrevit/__init__.py, line 35\n\nfrom pyrevit.compat import PY3, PY2\nVERSION_STRING = '0.0.'\nif PY3:\n    with open(op.join(op.dirname(__file__), 'version'), 'r', encoding='utf-8') as version_file:\n        VERSION_STRING = version_file.read()\nelse:\n    with open(op.join(op.dirname(__file__), 'version'), 'r') as version_file:\n        VERSION_STRING = version_file.read()\n", "hints_text": "Hi, \nGood issue report\nHave you tested the fixed you are proposing?\nIf so, and it works, feel free to make a PR and indicate the steps to test it.\nHi @jmcouffin,\n\nYes, I have tested the fix and can confirm it works on my machine.\nI will create a PR for this shortly.\n\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi, \nGood issue report\nHave you tested the fixed you are proposing?\nIf so, and it works, feel free to make a PR and indicate the steps to test it.\nHi @jmcouffin,\n\nYes, I have tested the fix and can confirm it works on my machine.\nI will create a PR for this shortly.\n\n\n> Hi [@jmcouffin](https://github.com/jmcouffin),\n> \n> Yes, I have tested the fix and can confirm it works on my machine. I will create a PR for this shortly.\n\nConfirmed, the proposed snippet works\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/e630790033c64879065cf62013281aa6fe1b42f8", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/31e5826e92b0e987097794fb53fcf18a8c104fd7", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/d26075d8e0a158a0c80abf0512f1ca71afda7fc3"], "created_at": "2025-09-12T06:23:41Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2811, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2811", "issue_numbers": [2810], "base_commit": "6332a36677b9f659064dc3fab2944b3331db73fc", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\nindex 011c8c3370..a3ebcd51bf 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\n@@ -21,7 +21,12 @@\n \n from __future__ import print_function\n import os.path as op\n-import itertools\n+import sys\n+from pyrevit.compat import PY2, PY3\n+if PY2:\n+    from itertools import izip_longest as zip_longest\n+elif PY3:\n+    from itertools import zip_longest\n \n from pyrevit import HOST_APP, EXEC_PARAMS\n from pyrevit import framework\n@@ -543,6 +548,8 @@ def print_md(md_str):\n         markdown_html = markdown_html.replace('\\n', '').replace('\\r', '')\n         html_code = coreutils.prepare_html_str(markdown_html)\n         print(html_code, end=\"\")\n+        if PY3:\n+            sys.stdout.flush()\n \n     def print_table(self, table_data, columns=None, formats=None,\n                     title='', last_line_style=''):\n@@ -579,7 +586,6 @@ def print_table(self, table_data, columns=None, formats=None,\n             self.add_style('tr:last-child {{ {style} }}'\n                            .format(style=last_line_style))\n \n-        zipper = itertools.izip_longest #pylint: disable=E1101\n         adjust_base_col = '|'\n         adjust_extra_col = ':---|'\n         base_col = '|'\n@@ -591,7 +597,7 @@ def print_table(self, table_data, columns=None, formats=None,\n         header = ''\n         if columns:\n             header = base_col\n-            for idx, col_name in zipper(range(max_col), columns, fillvalue=''): #pylint: disable=W0612\n+            for idx, col_name in zip_longest(range(max_col), columns, fillvalue=''): #pylint: disable=W0612\n                 header += extra_col.format(data=col_name)\n \n             header += '\\n'\n@@ -606,7 +612,7 @@ def print_table(self, table_data, columns=None, formats=None,\n         for entry in table_data:\n             row = base_col\n             for idx, attrib, attr_format \\\n-                    in zipper(range(max_col), entry, formats, fillvalue=''):\n+                    in zip_longest(range(max_col), entry, formats, fillvalue=''):\n                 if attr_format:\n                     value = attr_format.format(attrib)\n                 else:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: output.print_table() won't work for IPY3\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nI think this is due to izip_longest being renamed to zip_longest in IPY3. I'll try to fix it after some testing\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nFile \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\\pyrevitlib\\pyrevit\\output\\__init__.py\", line 582, in print_table\nAttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'izip_longest'\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nmaster | Branch: \"master\" | Version: \"5.2.0.25181+1332\" | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\"\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/30005e72656e906c2f8118025d4a4a0a928e0b9e", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/62eaf5de30fd888c4ec9d2c3116d7525a9988fbd", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/ad8a199f92fd6d631c78ee302be6fae39aa65b75"], "created_at": "2025-09-23T09:57:53Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2819, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2819", "issue_numbers": [2818], "base_commit": "118db80178c86b37b96ce4fae4163c01ac66a971", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/ensure.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/ensure.py\nindex d841e3be4e..771e4a3e6a 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/ensure.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/ensure.py\n@@ -1,11 +1,13 @@\n \"\"\"Idempotent operations to ensure a database object exists.\"\"\"\n import os.path as op\n \n+from System import Int64\n+\n from pyrevit import HOST_APP, DOCS, PyRevitException\n from pyrevit import coreutils\n from pyrevit.coreutils.logger import get_logger\n from pyrevit import DB\n-from pyrevit.revit import db\n+from pyrevit.compat import get_elementid_from_value_func\n from pyrevit.revit.db import query\n from pyrevit.revit.db import create\n from pyrevit.revit.db import transaction    #pylint: disable=E0611\n@@ -13,7 +15,7 @@\n \n #pylint: disable=W0703,C0302,C0103\n mlogger = get_logger(__name__)\n-\n+get_elementid_from_value = get_elementid_from_value_func()\n \n def ensure_sharedparam(sparam_name, sparam_categories, sparam_group,\n                        load_param=True, allow_vary_betwen_groups=False,\n@@ -75,8 +77,8 @@ def ensure_element_ids(mixed_list):\n             element_id_list.append(item.Id)\n         elif hasattr(item, 'Id') and isinstance(item.Id, DB.ElementId):\n             element_id_list.append(item.Id)\n-        elif isinstance(item, int):\n-            element_id_list.append(DB.ElementId(item))\n+        elif isinstance(item, (int, Int64)):\n+            element_id_list.append(get_elementid_from_value(item))\n \n     return element_id_list\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: revit.db.ensure - ensure_element_ids missing support for Revit>2024\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nhttps://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/blob/118db80178c86b37b96ce4fae4163c01ac66a971/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/revit/db/ensure.py#L78\n\nThis won't work anymore due to API changes. The value is no longer an int but rather Int64/long. A fix like this:\n\n```python\nfrom pyrevit.compat import get_elementid_from_value_func\nget_elementid_from_value = get_elementid_from_value_func()\ndef ensure_element_ids(mixed_list):\n...\n        elif isinstance(item, (int, Int64)):\n            element_id_list.append(get_elementid_from_value(item))\n```\n\nShould solve it. Strictly speaking the additional compat shouldn't be necessary, but there might be edge cases? I'll do a PR after testing.\n\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nWhen run with in Revit 2026, no output is generated by this function.\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\n==> Registered Clones (deployed from archive/image)\nmaster | Branch: \"master\" | Version: \"5.2.0.25181+1332\" | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\"\n==> Attachments\nmaster | Product: \"2026 First Customer Ship\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\" | AllUsers\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": ":package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25269+1336-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18039279690)\n:package: New work-