{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2848, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2848", "issue_numbers": [2847], "base_commit": "09cc70da221af9b3726b0e92f382db4cca4aba30", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/linkmaker.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/linkmaker.py\nindex 2761ff396c..ee12ac51c6 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/linkmaker.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/linkmaker.py\n@@ -1,7 +1,6 @@\n \"\"\"Handle creation of output window helper links.\"\"\"\n \n from pyrevit.compat import safe_strtype, get_elementid_value_func\n-from pyrevit import DB\n from pyrevit.coreutils.logger import get_logger\n \n \n@@ -63,7 +62,21 @@ def make_link(element_ids, contents=None):\n     link_title = ', '.join(strids)\n \n     if len(reviturl) >= 2000:\n-        alertjs = 'alert(&quot;Url was too long and discarded!&quot;);'\n+        total_length = 0\n+        max_elements = 0\n+        elementquery_parts = ['element[]=' + strid for strid in strids]\n+        for i, part in enumerate(elementquery_parts):\n+            if i > 0:\n+                total_length += 1  # for '&'\n+            total_length += len(part)\n+            if total_length >= 2000:\n+                break\n+            max_elements += 1\n+\n+        alertjs = \\\n+            'alert(&quot;URL was too long ({} characters). Maximum allowed is 2000. '\\\n+            'Only {} out of {} elements could fit.&quot;);'\\\n+            .format(len(reviturl), max_elements, len(strids))\n         linkattrs_select = 'href=\"#\" onClick=\"{}\"'.format(alertjs)\n         linkattrs_show = linkattrs_select\n     else:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "linkify too long error message isn't descriptive\n## Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe\n\nThis https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/blob/09cc70da221af9b3726b0e92f382db4cca4aba30/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/linkmaker.py#L66\nsimply gives you an error without any hint to fix it. \n\n## Describe the solution you'd like\n\nA hint of maximum allowed number elements\n\n## Describe alternatives you've considered\n\nFor my specific project this evalutes to about 100 elements. so i am chunking it up to have multiple links to click on\n\n## Additional context\n\nIf anyone has an idea on how to automatically chunk this into the linkify directly would be great. Otherwise I'll try to PR a more helpful error message.\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": ":package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25279+2157-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18295066215)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25280+0218-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18299649077)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25280+1054-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18310269110)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25280+1057-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18310340146)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25282+1656-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18383069168)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25283+0140-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18393860355)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25286+1022-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18462567444)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25287+0905-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18491229354)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25287+1000-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18492680756)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25288+0613-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18519499405)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+0755-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18645832215)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+0828-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18646543051)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+1113-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18650151549)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+1234-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18652061600)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25295+0707-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18708146912)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0824-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18742145801)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0837-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18742522215)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0923-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18743666516)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25300+1037-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18837909030)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1412-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18877067353)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1521-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18879814948)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0921-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18902895456)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0949-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18903650953)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+1503-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18912342699)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1644-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19042091369)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1935-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19045856684)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2011-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19047829653)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2045-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19048693375)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25307+2237-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19051437715)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25308+0721-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19060884416)\n:package: New public release are available for [5.3.0.25307+2146](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases/tag/untagged-aa53b69f63e7f42540bc)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/778a7d711abe9255ee0978777addc095222ac14a"], "created_at": "2025-10-06T17:45:30Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2877, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2877", "issue_numbers": [2856], "base_commit": "a1a70310d66dbbc428111f143736f4392b4ee9b0", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/bundle.yaml b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\nindex 8b5064a779..97a7714679 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\n@@ -49,5 +49,6 @@ tooltip:\n     \n author: BIMOne Inc.(2021), Nonica (Jaime Alonso Candau - 2023), BIMOne Inc. (Jean-Marc Couffin - 2023)\n engine:\n+  clean: true\n   persistent: true\n   full_frame: true\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Color Elements by Parameter\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [ ] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [ ] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [ ] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [ ] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nColor Splasher tool generates repeating error whenever instances are selected in a view. There are two instances of the error that occur. \n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nColor Elements by Parameter\n\nUnhandled exception has occurred in a component in your application. If you click Continue, the application will ignore this error and attempt to continue.\n\nname 'DataTable' is not defined.\n\n_______________________________________________________________________\n\nColor Elements by Parameter\n\nUnhandled exception has occurred in a component in your application. If you click Continue, the application will ignore this error and attempt to continue \n\nname 'external_event_trace' is not defined.\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n1. Go to pyRevit\n2. Click on Color Splasher\n3. Select instance parameter (ex. Walls)\n4. See error\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\nI have seen tutorials where I follow the same steps in a view to color every instance of selected family, and a range of colors appears and lets you do an array of things to color code model.\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nPID: 31980 | 2024.3.3 | Version: 24.3.30.11 | Build: 20250516_1515(x64) | Language: 0 | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\Autodesk\\Revit 2024\"\n\nMicrosoft Windows 10 [Version 10.0.26100]\n\nLatest Installed .Net Framework: 8.0.11\n\npyRevit CLI v5.2.0.25181+1332.ad837f1fc6ac89979e64710991eb6d846b63c109\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "This is a known issue and not fixable at the moment.\nCurrent fix involves using the pyrevit `reload` button\n\nThanks \n> This is a known issue and not fixable at the moment. Current fix involves using the pyrevit `reload` button\n> \n> Thanks\n\nIf reloading fixes it, wouldn't a engine clean in the bundle yaml also fix it? Still no real fix, but better than reload?\n\n", "all_hints_text": "This is a known issue and not fixable at the moment.\nCurrent fix involves using the pyrevit `reload` button\n\nThanks \n> This is a known issue and not fixable at the moment. Current fix involves using the pyrevit `reload` button\n> \n> Thanks\n\nIf reloading fixes it, wouldn't a engine clean in the bundle yaml also fix it? Still no real fix, but better than reload?\n> engine clean\n\nGood suggestion @Wurschdhaud fixed by #2877\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/545fbfd87284118d0444af81dc44ab1473a4b5c5"], "created_at": "2025-10-22T07:04:10Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2872, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2872", "issue_numbers": [2863], "base_commit": "37016a4b0a755086547f7fa8ab930a9d17658c1b", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py\nindex c0337a4ed1..5c7ddca718 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py\n@@ -781,6 +781,17 @@ def set_tooltip_video(self, tooltip_video):\n                 _StackPanel = System.Windows.Controls.StackPanel()\n                 _video = System.Windows.Controls.MediaElement()\n                 _video.Source = Uri(tooltip_video)\n+                _video.LoadedBehavior = System.Windows.Controls.MediaState.Manual\n+                _video.UnloadedBehavior = System.Windows.Controls.MediaState.Manual\n+\n+                def on_media_ended(sender, args):\n+                    sender.Position = System.TimeSpan.Zero\n+                    sender.Play()\n+                _video.MediaEnded += on_media_ended\n+\n+                def on_loaded(sender, args):\n+                    sender.Play()\n+                _video.Loaded += on_loaded\n                 _StackPanel.Children.Add(_video)\n                 adwindows_obj.ToolTip.ExpandedContent = _StackPanel\n                 adwindows_obj.ResolveToolTip()\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: tooltip video starts delayed\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\nThe tooltip video starts delayed, for me after like 3-5s. I assume this is due to loading times of the tooltip hover window.\nThis means really short tooltips won't show any video at all, only the last frame.\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nsee above\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\nEither delayed playback, or, maybe even better, let the video loop.\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\n==> Registered Clones (deployed from archive/image)\nmaster | Branch: \"master\" | Version: \"5.2.0.25181+1332\" | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\"\n==> Attachments\nmaster | Product: \"2026 First Customer Ship\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\" | AllUsers\nmaster | Product: \"Autodesk Revit 2024\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\" | AllUsers\nmaster | Product: \"2022.1.8\" | Engine: DEFAULT (2712) | Path: \"C:\\Program Files\\pyRevit-Master\" | AllUsers\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "## AI suggested approach:\n\n#### Where It's Generated\nThe tooltip video is set up in the _PyRevitRibbonButton class's set_tooltip_video() method. ribbon.py:771-791 This method creates a System.Windows.Controls.MediaElement to display the video and adds it to the tooltip's expanded content. ribbon.py:782-786\n\nThe video file is discovered and applied during UI creation in uimaker.py, where buttons are created with their tooltip_media parameter. uimaker.py:202\n\n#### Current Playback Behavior\nCurrently, the video playback behavior is not configurable. The MediaElement is created with default settings, which means:\n\nNo delayed start\nNo looping\nPlays once when the tooltip is shown\n#### How to Change Playback Behavior\nTo modify the playback behavior, you would need to edit the set_tooltip_video() method in pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py. Here's what you could add:\n\nFor looping: Add _video.LoadedBehavior = System.Windows.Controls.MediaState.Manual and handle the MediaEnded event to restart playback.\n\nFor delayed start: You would need to add event handlers or use a timer to delay the Play() call.\n\nThe relevant code was last modified by Davide Giannuzzi on 2023-02-27 in commit [9dab3b6b](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/9dab3b6b), with additional changes by Jean-Marc Couffin on 2024-08-13 in commit [3eed7c79](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/3eed7c79).\n\n#### Notes\nThe tooltip video feature uses WPF's MediaElement control, which supports various playback properties like LoadedBehavior, UnloadedBehavior, and events like MediaEnded. However, pyRevit's current implementation doesn't expose these configuration options. If you need custom playback behavior, you would need to modify the source code directly in ribbon.py or submit a feature request/pull request to add configuration options for video playback behavior.\n\n\n## and google search:\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/desktop/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-repeat-media-playback\n\n", "all_hints_text": "## AI suggested approach:\n\n#### Where It's Generated\nThe tooltip video is set up in the _PyRevitRibbonButton class's set_tooltip_video() method. ribbon.py:771-791 This method creates a System.Windows.Controls.MediaElement to display the video and adds it to the tooltip's expanded content. ribbon.py:782-786\n\nThe video file is discovered and applied during UI creation in uimaker.py, where buttons are created with their tooltip_media parameter. uimaker.py:202\n\n#### Current Playback Behavior\nCurrently, the video playback behavior is not configurable. The MediaElement is created with default settings, which means:\n\nNo delayed start\nNo looping\nPlays once when the tooltip is shown\n#### How to Change Playback Behavior\nTo modify the playback behavior, you would need to edit the set_tooltip_video() method in pyrevitlib/pyrevit/coreutils/ribbon.py. Here's what you could add:\n\nFor looping: Add _video.LoadedBehavior = System.Windows.Controls.MediaState.Manual and handle the MediaEnded event to restart playback.\n\nFor delayed start: You would need to add event handlers or use a timer to delay the Play() call.\n\nThe relevant code was last modified by Davide Giannuzzi on 2023-02-27 in commit [9dab3b6b](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/9dab3b6b), with additional changes by Jean-Marc Couffin on 2024-08-13 in commit [3eed7c79](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/3eed7c79).\n\n#### Notes\nThe tooltip video feature uses WPF's MediaElement control, which supports various playback properties like LoadedBehavior, UnloadedBehavior, and events like MediaEnded. However, pyRevit's current implementation doesn't expose these configuration options. If you need custom playback behavior, you would need to modify the source code directly in ribbon.py or submit a feature request/pull request to add configuration options for video playback behavior.\n\n\n## and google search:\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/desktop/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-repeat-media-playback\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+0828-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18646543051)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+1113-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18650151549)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25293+1234-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18652061600)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25295+0707-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18708146912)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0824-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18742145801)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0837-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18742522215)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25296+0923-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18743666516)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25300+1037-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18837909030)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1412-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18877067353)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1521-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18879814948)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0921-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18902895456)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0949-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18903650953)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+1503-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18912342699)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1644-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19042091369)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1935-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19045856684)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2011-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19047829653)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2045-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19048693375)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25307+2237-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19051437715)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25308+0721-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19060884416)\n:package: New public release are available for [5.3.0.25307+2146](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases/tag/untagged-aa53b69f63e7f42540bc)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/b2683c397b338f38daf41519f9babe7948738814"], "created_at": "2025-10-18T17:22:15Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2876, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2876", "issue_numbers": [2870], "base_commit": "b75caa6d27e558cee0f991174c84f75e4c8f5753", "patch": "diff --git a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\nindex 7e5f817eb6..bab1c3f04b 100644\n--- a/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\n+++ b/pyrevitlib/pyrevit/output/__init__.py\n@@ -552,8 +552,83 @@ def print_md(md_str):\n             sys.stdout.flush()\n \n \n+    def print_table(self, table_data, columns=None, formats=None,\n+                    title='', last_line_style=''):\n+        \"\"\"Print provided data in a table in output window.\n+\n+        Args:\n+            table_data (list[iterable[Any]]): 2D array of data\n+            title (str): table title\n+            columns (list[str]): list of column names\n+            formats (list[str]): column data formats\n+            last_line_style (str): css style of last row\n+\n+        Examples:\n+            ```python\n+            data = [\n+            ['row1', 'data', 'data', 80 ],\n+            ['row2', 'data', 'data', 45 ],\n+            ]\n+            output.print_table(\n+            table_data=data,\n+            title=\"Example Table\",\n+            columns=[\"Row Name\", \"Column 1\", \"Column 2\", \"Percentage\"],\n+            formats=['', '', '', '{}%'],\n+            last_line_style='color:red;'\n+            )\n+            ```\n+        \"\"\"\n+        if not columns:\n+            columns = []\n+        if not formats:\n+            formats = []\n+\n+        if last_line_style:\n+            self.add_style('tr:last-child {{ {style} }}'\n+                           .format(style=last_line_style))\n+\n+        zipper = zip_longest #pylint: disable=E1101\n+        adjust_base_col = '|'\n+        adjust_extra_col = ':---|'\n+        base_col = '|'\n+        extra_col = '{data}|'\n+\n+        # find max column count\n+        max_col = max([len(x) for x in table_data])\n+\n+        header = ''\n+        if columns:\n+            header = base_col\n+            for idx, col_name in zipper(range(max_col), columns, fillvalue=''): #pylint: disable=W0612\n+                header += extra_col.format(data=col_name)\n+\n+            header += '\\n'\n+\n+        justifier = adjust_base_col\n+        for idx in range(max_col):\n+            justifier += adjust_extra_col\n+\n+        justifier += '\\n'\n+\n+        rows = ''\n+        for entry in table_data:\n+            row = base_col\n+            for idx, attrib, attr_format \\\n+                    in zipper(range(max_col), entry, formats, fillvalue=''):\n+                if attr_format:\n+                    value = attr_format.format(attrib)\n+                else:\n+                    value = attrib\n+                row += extra_col.format(data=value)\n+            rows += row + '\\n'\n+\n+        table = header + justifier + rows\n+        self.print_md('### {title}'.format(title=title))\n+        self.print_md(table)\n+\n+\n     def table_html_header(self, columns, table_uid, border_style):\n-        \"\"\"Helper method for print_table() method\n+        \"\"\"Helper method for print_html_table() method\n \n         Return html <thead><tr><th> row for the table header\n         \n@@ -569,7 +644,7 @@ def table_html_header(self, columns, table_uid, border_style):\n             ```python\n             output = pyrevit.output.get_output()\n             \n-            # Basic usage - called internally by print_table()\n+            # Basic usage - called internally by print_html_table()\n             columns = [\"Name\", \"Age\", \"City\"]\n             table_uid = 1\n             border_style = \"border: 1px solid black;\"\n@@ -608,11 +683,11 @@ def table_check_input_lists(self,\n                                 columns,\n                                 formats,\n                                 input_kwargs):\n-        \"\"\"Helper method for print_table() method\n+        \"\"\"Helper method for print_html_table() method\n         \n         Check that the table_data is present and is a list\n         Check that table_data rows are of the same length\n-        Check that all print_table() kwargs of type list are of correct length\n+        Check that all print_html_table() kwargs of type list are of correct length\n \n         Args:\n             table_data (list[list[Any]]): The whole table data as 2D list\n@@ -684,14 +759,14 @@ def table_check_input_lists(self,\n             if not kwarg_list: # No kwarg is OK beacause they are optional\n                 continue\n             if not isinstance(kwarg_list, list):\n-                return False, \"One of the print_table kwargs that should be a list is not a list ({})\".format(kwarg_list)\n+                return False, \"One of the print_html_table kwargs that should be a list is not a list ({})\".format(kwarg_list)\n             if len(kwarg_list) != len_data_row:\n-                return False, \"print_table kwarg list length problem (should match {} columns)\".format(len_data_row)\n+                return False, \"print_html_table kwarg list length problem (should match {} columns)\".format(len_data_row)\n \n         return True, \"Inputs OK\"\n \n \n-    def print_table(self,\n+    def print_html_table(self,\n                     table_data,\n                     columns=None,\n                     formats=None,\n@@ -722,7 +797,7 @@ def print_table(self,\n             ['row1', 'data', 'data', 80 ],\n             ['row2', 'data', 'data', 45 ],\n             ]\n-            output.print_table(\n+            output.print_html_table(\n             table_data=data,\n             title=\"Example Table\",\n             columns=[\"Row Name\", \"Column 1\", \"Column 2\", \"Percentage\"],\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: print_table no longer respects markdown since #2827\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\n<img width=\"412\" height=\"127\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c374957b-b5cc-4d15-b028-150829140d07\" />\n\ni believe it's related to #2827 \n\nbefore it was like this:\n\n<img width=\"384\" height=\"169\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f5f0858e-d51e-4aff-808c-f70ba2a79701\" />\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nsee above\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\nUse latest develop / WIP build\ncreate a table with bold content (or run e.g. count faces)\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nlatest wip\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "@nasmovk can you check it out?\nYes. I'll, look into it. \n@Wurschdhaud can you give an example of how you use markdown inside table output?\nI admit I did not consider you might need to do this, mix markdown in html table.\nSo maybe we should have a discussion of whether it is a good idea to modify the existing print_table.\nIt might be better to add a new method (named print_html_table or something) that is more based on pure HTML with CSS.\nThen we could improve this over time while leaving the legacy markdown-based print_table.\n@jmcouffin any thoughts.\nI know @sanzoghenzo had some thoughts on the subject.\n@nasmovk I added a second screenshot to the bug report. Don't know how many tools, inside pyrevit or 3rd party, are affected by this, and if sth similiar can be achieved with your improved table function\nThanks for the second screenshot.\nSo your data for the cell is just a string using MD syntax.\nI think existing tools inside pyRevit do not use this way of formatting with table output. It is not really mentioned in the documentation which I why I did not consider it.\nIt is not possible to know how many personal tools might use your approach. I am happy to rollback and postpone my new method. Or as I suggest above, we could maintain two methods, one MD-based and the other more CSS-based.\nMy current implementation in #2827 does not provide a formatting option for individual cells. You could acheive the same I think by using HTML & CSS in you cell data string.\n> print_html_table\n\nIt sounds like a plan.\nI wouldn't mind having this as a new method. \nOr you could change the print_table() with an argument default to MD on one side.\n> I know [@sanzoghenzo](https://github.com/sanzoghenzo) had some thoughts on the subject.\n\nFound it https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io/t/pyrevit-output-table-formatting/1532/11?u=sanzoghenzo\n\nMaybe it was just pure luck, but even then I suggested creating a _new method_ and not overwriting the current one :wink:\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@nasmovk can you check it out?\nYes. I'll, look into it. \n@Wurschdhaud can you give an example of how you use markdown inside table output?\nI admit I did not consider you might need to do this, mix markdown in html table.\nSo maybe we should have a discussion of whether it is a good idea to modify the existing print_table.\nIt might be better to add a new method (named print_html_table or something) that is more based on pure HTML with CSS.\nThen we could improve this over time while leaving the legacy markdown-based print_table.\n@jmcouffin any thoughts.\nI know @sanzoghenzo had some thoughts on the subject.\n@nasmovk I added a second screenshot to the bug report. Don't know how many tools, inside pyrevit or 3rd party, are affected by this, and if sth similiar can be achieved with your improved table function\nThanks for the second screenshot.\nSo your data for the cell is just a string using MD syntax.\nI think existing tools inside pyRevit do not use this way of formatting with table output. It is not really mentioned in the documentation which I why I did not consider it.\nIt is not possible to know how many personal tools might use your approach. I am happy to rollback and postpone my new method. Or as I suggest above, we could maintain two methods, one MD-based and the other more CSS-based.\nMy current implementation in #2827 does not provide a formatting option for individual cells. You could acheive the same I think by using HTML & CSS in you cell data string.\n> print_html_table\n\nIt sounds like a plan.\nI wouldn't mind having this as a new method. \nOr you could change the print_table() with an argument default to MD on one side.\n> I know [@sanzoghenzo](https://github.com/sanzoghenzo) had some thoughts on the subject.\n\nFound it https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io/t/pyrevit-output-table-formatting/1532/11?u=sanzoghenzo\n\nMaybe it was just pure luck, but even then I suggested creating a _new method_ and not overwriting the current one :wink:\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/8570095e513689f8ceb6607da2c527cfcc970c44"], "created_at": "2025-10-20T10:34:52Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2886, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2886", "issue_numbers": [2885], "base_commit": "a66603d36dbe25eeff20992dc9da3ac417af50e4", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/checks/mysuperdupercheck-check.py b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/checks/mysuperdupercheck-check.py\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex c397b6d933..0000000000\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/checks/mysuperdupercheck-check.py\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,77 +0,0 @@\n-# -*- coding: UTF-8 -*-\n-from pyrevit import script, revit, DB, DOCS\n-from pyrevit.preflight import PreflightTestCase\n-\n-doc = DOCS.doc\n-\n-\n-def grids_collector(document):\n-    return DB.FilteredElementCollector(document).OfCategory(DB.BuiltInCategory.OST_Grids).WhereElementIsNotElementType()\n-\n-\n-def grids_count(document=doc):\n-    grids = grids_collector(document)\n-    return grids.GetElementCount()\n-\n-\n-def grids_names(document=doc):\n-    grids = grids_collector(document)\n-    return [grid.Name for grid in grids]\n-\n-\n-def grids_types(document=doc):\n-    grids = grids_collector(document)\n-    grids_types = []\n-    for grid in grids:\n-        grid_type = document.GetElement(grid.GetTypeId())\n-        # grid_type = grid.get_Parameter(DB.BuiltInParameter.ELEM_TYPE_PARAM).AsElement()\n-        grids_types.append(grid_type.get_Parameter(DB.BuiltInParameter.SYMBOL_NAME_PARAM).AsString())\n-    return grids_types\n-\n-\n-def grids_pinned(document=doc):\n-    grids = grids_collector(document)\n-    return [grid.Pinned for grid in grids]\n-\n-\n-def grids_scoped(document=doc):\n-    grids = grids_collector(document)\n-    scoped_grids = []\n-    for grid in grids:\n-        scope = grid.get_Parameter(DB.BuiltInParameter.DATUM_VOLUME_OF_INTEREST).AsElementId()\n-        scope = document.GetElement(scope)\n-        if scope:\n-            scoped_grids.append(scope.Name)\n-        else:\n-            scoped_grids.append(\"None\")\n-    return scoped_grids\n-\n-\n-def check_model(doc, output):\n-    output = script.get_output()\n-    output.close_others()\n-    output.print_md(\"# Grids Data Lister\")\n-    count = grids_count()\n-    output.print_md(\"## Number of grids: {0}\".format(count))\n-    names = grids_names() # [1,2,3,4]\n-    types = grids_types() # [bubble, bubble, bubble, bubble]\n-    pinned = grids_pinned() # [True, False, True, False]\n-    scoper = grids_scoped() # [Name of scope, Name of scope, Name of scope, Name of scope]\n-    output.print_table(table_data=zip(names, types, pinned, scoper), title=\"Grids\", columns=[\"Name\", \"Type\", \"Pinned\", \"Scope Box\"])\n-\n-\n-\n-class ModelChecker(PreflightTestCase):\n-    \"\"\"\n-    List grids, if they are pinned, scoped boxed, or named\n-\n-    This QC tools returns you with the following data:\n-        Grids count, name, type, pinned status\n-\n-    \"\"\"\n-\n-    name = \"Grids Data Lister\"\n-    author = \"Jean-Marc Couffin\"\n-\n-    def startTest(self, doc, output):\n-        check_model(doc, output)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug]: Grids Data Lister appearing twice in preflight check\n### \u2708 Pre-Flight checks\n\n- [x] I **don't have SentinelOne** antivirus installed (see above for the solution)\n- [x] I have **searched in the issues** (open and closed) but couldn't find a similar issue\n- [x] I have **searched in the [pyRevit Forum](https://discourse.pyrevitlabs.io)** for similar issues\n- [x] I already **followed the [installation troubleshooting guide](https://pyrevitlabs.notion.site/Installation-issues-f6495adb56254e9e8021f8a68e3b2ab7) thoroughly**\n- [x] I am using the **latest pyRevit Version**\n\n### \ud83d\udc1e Describe the bug\n\n<img width=\"543\" height=\"201\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/44c3c2a8-9dcc-4ecc-833e-0181e4e105bd\" />\n\nThese two are nearly identical and are the reason there are two.\n\n<img width=\"256\" height=\"144\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/83b33edc-8eab-4956-8280-1e4b2dc31a11\" />\n\n### \u2328 Error/Debug Message\n\n```shell\nsee above\n```\n\n### \u267b\ufe0f To Reproduce\n\n_No response_\n\n### \u23f2\ufe0f Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### \ud83d\udda5\ufe0f Hardware and Software Setup (please complete the following information)\n\n```shell\nlatest non wip release\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n", "hints_text": "Good catch. You can remove the one you feel makes less sense\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Good catch. You can remove the one you feel makes less sense\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25300+1037-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18837909030)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1412-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18877067353)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25301+1521-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18879814948)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0921-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18902895456)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+0949-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18903650953)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25302+1503-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/18912342699)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1644-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19042091369)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+1935-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19045856684)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2011-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19047829653)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.2.0.25307+2045-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19048693375)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25307+2237-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19051437715)\n:package: New work-in-progress (wip) builds are available for [5.3.0.25308+0721-wip](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/actions/runs/19060884416)\n:package: New public release are available for [5.3.0.25307+2146](https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/releases/tag/untagged-aa53b69f63e7f42540bc)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/3620277fd758db81e31f26a20bb29af3c776d6cf"], "created_at": "2025-10-27T09:36:34Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 3127, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-3127", "issue_numbers": [2889], "base_commit": "62dc9292e3af686aee51da0fe136870a61cd6ff0", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/bundle.yaml b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\nindex 3128e7efb6..d8ee374eb5 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/bundle.yaml\n@@ -7,11 +7,11 @@ title:\n   de_de: Umummerieren\n   pt_br: Renumerar\n tooltip:\n-  en_us: ReNumber numbered elements in order of selection\n-  fr_fr: Renum\u00e9roter les \u00e9l\u00e9ments dans l'ordre de s\u00e9lection\n-  ru: \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u044f\u0434\u043a\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f.\n-  chinese_s: \u6309\u7167\u9009\u62e9\u987a\u5e8f\uff0c\u4e3a\u5df2\u7f16\u53f7\u7684\u56fe\u5143\u91cd\u65b0\u7f16\u53f7\n-  es_es: Renumerar elementos numerados en orden de selecci\u00f3n\n-  de_de: Elemente werden mit der Reihenfolge der Auswahl neu nummeriert\n-  pt_br: Renumerar elementos numerados na ordem de sele\u00e7\u00e3o\n+  en_us: ReNumber numbered elements in order of selection. Shift-Click to choose duplicate handling (Alert, Skip, or Sweep).\n+  fr_fr: Renum\u00e9roter les \u00e9l\u00e9ments dans l'ordre de s\u00e9lection. Maj+Clic pour g\u00e9rer les doublons (Alerte, Ignorer ou Balayer).\n+  ru: \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u044d\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u044f\u0434\u043a\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f. Shift+\u041a\u043b\u0438\u043a \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u044b\u0431\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u043a\u0438 \u0434\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0439 (\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435, \u041f\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0443\u0441\u043a \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0421\u043a\u0432\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0443\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f).\n+  chinese_s: \u6309\u7167\u9009\u62e9\u987a\u5e8f\uff0c\u4e3a\u5df2\u7f16\u53f7\u7684\u56fe\u5143\u91cd\u65b0\u7f16\u53f7\u3002\u6309\u4f4f Shift \u5355\u51fb\u53ef\u9009\u62e9\u91cd\u590d\u9879\u5904\u7406\u65b9\u5f0f\uff08\u63d0\u793a\u3001\u8df3\u8fc7\u6216\u8986\u76d6\uff09\u3002\n+  es_es: Renumerar elementos numerados en orden de selecci\u00f3n. Shift+Clic para gestionar duplicados (Alerta, Omitir o Barrer).\n+  de_de: Elemente werden mit der Reihenfolge der Auswahl neu nummeriert. Shift+Klick zur Behandlung von Duplikaten (Warnung, \u00dcberspringen oder Durchnummerieren).\n+  pt_br: Renumerar elementos numerados na ordem de sele\u00e7\u00e3o. Shift+Clique para lidar com duplicatas (Alerta, Ignorar ou Varrer).\n author: '{{author}}'\ndiff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/script.py b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/script.py\nindex f9f13bc495..7678bca497 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/script.py\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Modify.panel/edit2.stack/ReNumber.pushbutton/script.py\n@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@\n+# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n \"\"\"ReNumber numbered elements in order of selection.\"\"\"\n #pylint: disable=import-error,invalid-name,broad-except\n from collections import OrderedDict\n@@ -6,7 +7,7 @@\n from pyrevit import revit, DB\n from pyrevit import coreutils\n from pyrevit import forms\n-from pyrevit import script\n+from pyrevit import script, EXEC_PARAMS\n \n doc = revit.doc\n uidoc = revit.uidoc\n@@ -23,6 +24,9 @@\n     DB.ViewSection,\n     DB.ViewSheet,\n )\n+DUPE_MODE_SWEEP = \"Sweep (renumber displaced)\"  # default behaviour\n+DUPE_MODE_ALERT = \"Alert (warn and skip)\"\n+DUPE_MODE_SKIP = \"Skip (already numbered)\"\n \n \n class RNOpts(object):\n@@ -146,7 +150,7 @@ def increment(number):\n \n \n def get_number(target_element):\n-    \"\"\"Get target elemnet number (might be from Number or other fields)\"\"\"\n+    \"\"\"Get target element number (might be from Number or other fields)\"\"\"\n     if hasattr(target_element, \"Number\"):\n         return target_element.Number\n \n@@ -162,7 +166,7 @@ def get_number(target_element):\n \n \n def set_number(target_element, new_number):\n-    \"\"\"Set target elemnet number (might be at Number or other fields)\"\"\"\n+    \"\"\"Set target element number (might be at Number or other fields)\"\"\"\n     if hasattr(target_element, \"Number\"):\n         target_element.Number = new_number\n         return\n@@ -227,34 +231,52 @@ def find_replacement_number(existing_number, elements_dict):\n     return replaced_number\n \n \n-def renumber_element(target_views, target_element, new_number, elements_dict):\n-    \"\"\"Renumber given element.\"\"\"\n-    # check if elements with same number exists\n+def renumber_element(target_views, target_element, new_number,\n+                     elements_dict, dupe_mode=DUPE_MODE_SWEEP):\n+    \"\"\"Renumber given element, respecting the chosen duplicate-handling mode.\"\"\"\n+\n+    # \u2500\u2500 duplicate check \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n     if new_number in elements_dict:\n-        element_with_same_number = \\\n-            revit.doc.GetElement(elements_dict[new_number])\n-        # make sure its not the same as target_element\n+        element_with_same_number = revit.doc.GetElement(elements_dict[new_number])\n+\n         if element_with_same_number \\\n                 and element_with_same_number.Id != target_element.Id:\n-            # replace its number with something else that is not conflicting\n-            current_number = get_number(element_with_same_number)\n-            replaced_number = \\\n-                find_replacement_number(current_number, elements_dict)\n-            set_number(element_with_same_number, replaced_number)\n-            # record the element with its new number for later renumber jobs\n-            elements_dict[replaced_number] = element_with_same_number.Id\n-\n-    # check if target element is already listed\n-    # remove the existing number entry since we are renumbering\n+\n+            if dupe_mode == DUPE_MODE_ALERT:\n+                forms.alert(\n+                    \"Duplicate number \\\"{}\\\" found.\\n\"\n+                    \"Element skipped.\".format(new_number),\n+                    title=\"Duplicate Element Found\"\n+                )\n+                return   # abort \u2013 do not renumber this element\n+\n+            elif dupe_mode == DUPE_MODE_SKIP:\n+                # silently skip if the target itself is already numbered\n+                # (i.e. it has *any* number set \u2013 user probably tagged it already)\n+                if get_number(target_element):\n+                    return\n+                # if target has no number yet, fall through to sweep behaviour\n+                # so it still gets a free slot\n+                current_number = get_number(element_with_same_number)\n+                replaced_number = find_replacement_number(current_number, elements_dict)\n+                set_number(element_with_same_number, replaced_number)\n+                elements_dict[replaced_number] = element_with_same_number.Id\n+\n+            else:  # DUPE_MODE_SWEEP \u2013 original behaviour\n+                current_number = get_number(element_with_same_number)\n+                replaced_number = find_replacement_number(current_number, elements_dict)\n+                set_number(element_with_same_number, replaced_number)\n+                elements_dict[replaced_number] = element_with_same_number.Id\n+\n+    # \u2500\u2500 remove stale entry for this element \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n     existing_number = get_number(target_element)\n     if existing_number in elements_dict:\n         elements_dict.pop(existing_number)\n \n-    # renumber the given element\n+    # \u2500\u2500 apply the new number \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n     logger.debug('applying %s', new_number)\n     set_number(target_element, new_number)\n     elements_dict[new_number] = target_element.Id\n-    # mark the element visually to renumbered\n     mark_element_as_renumbered(target_views, target_element)\n \n \n@@ -272,42 +294,34 @@ def _unmark_collected(category_name, target_views, renumbered_element_ids):\n         unmark_renamed_elements(target_views, renumbered_element_ids)\n \n \n-def pick_and_renumber(rnopts, starting_index, pb):\n+def pick_and_renumber(rnopts, starting_index, pb, dupe_mode=DUPE_MODE_SWEEP):\n     \"\"\"Main renumbering routine for elements of given category.\"\"\"\n-    # all actions under one transaction\n     if rnopts.bicat != BIC.OST_Viewports:\n         open_views = get_open_views()\n     else:\n         open_views = [revit.active_view]\n     with revit.TransactionGroup(\"Renumber {}\".format(rnopts.name)):\n-        # make sure target elements are easily selectable\n         with EasilySelectableElements(open_views, rnopts.bicat):\n             index = starting_index\n-            # collect existing elements number:id data\n             existing_elements_data = get_elements_dict(open_views, rnopts.bicat)\n-            # dict to collect renumbered elements\n             renumbered_element_ids = {}\n-            # ask user to pick elements and renumber them\n             for picked_element in revit.get_picked_elements_by_category(\n                     rnopts.bicat,\n                     message=\"Select {} in order\".format(rnopts.name.lower())):\n-                # need nested transactions to push revit to update view\n-                # on each renumber task\n                 try:\n                     pb.update_progress(int(index), int(starting_index))\n                 except (ValueError, TypeError):\n                     pb.update_progress(0, 0)\n                 with revit.Transaction(\"Renumber {}\".format(rnopts.name)):\n-                    # record the renumbered element\n                     if picked_element.Id not in renumbered_element_ids:\n                         renumbered_element_ids[picked_element.Id] = {}\n                         for v in open_views:\n-                            renumbered_element_ids[picked_element.Id][v.Id] = v.GetElementOverrides(picked_element.Id)\n-                    # actual renumber task\n+                            renumbered_element_ids[picked_element.Id][v.Id] = \\\n+                                v.GetElementOverrides(picked_element.Id)\n                     renumber_element(open_views, picked_element,\n-                                     index, existing_elements_data)\n+                                     index, existing_elements_data,\n+                                     dupe_mode=dupe_mode)\n                 index = increment(index)\n-            # unmark all renumbered elements\n             _unmark_collected(rnopts.name, open_views, renumbered_element_ids)\n \n \n@@ -428,7 +442,19 @@ def update_progress(self, value, max_value):\n             width=400\n         )\n \n+\n     if selected_option_name:\n+        dupe_mode = DUPE_MODE_SWEEP   # normal click \u2192 original behaviour\n+        if EXEC_PARAMS.config_mode:\n+            chosen = forms.CommandSwitchWindow.show(\n+                [DUPE_MODE_ALERT, DUPE_MODE_SKIP, DUPE_MODE_SWEEP],\n+                message=\"How should duplicate numbers be handled?\",\n+                title=\"Advanced: Duplicate Handling\",\n+                width=420\n+            )\n+            if not chosen:\n+                script.exit()\n+            dupe_mode = chosen\n         selected_option = options_dict[selected_option_name]\n         if selected_option.by_bicat:\n             # if renumber doors by room\n@@ -438,6 +464,10 @@ def update_progress(self, value, max_value):\n                     title=\"Pick Pairs of Door and Room. ESCAPE to end.\"\n                 ):\n                     door_by_room_renumber(selected_option)\n+                    # NOTE: door_by_room_renumber calls renumber_element internally.\n+                    # To fully support dupe_mode there too, pass it through\n+                    # door_by_room_renumber(selected_option, dupe_mode=dupe_mode)\n+                    # and add the same dupe_mode param to that function.\n \n         else:\n             starting_number = ask_for_starting_number(selected_option.name)\n@@ -456,9 +486,9 @@ def update_progress(self, value, max_value):\n                         )\n                     ) as pb:\n                         pb.update_progress(_start_int, _start_int)\n-                        pick_and_renumber(selected_option, starting_number, pb)\n+                        pick_and_renumber(selected_option, starting_number, pb, dupe_mode=dupe_mode)\n                 else:\n                     with forms.WarningBar(\n                         title=\"Pick {} One by One. ESCAPE to end.\".format(selected_option.name)\n                     ):\n-                        pick_and_renumber(selected_option, starting_number, _NoOpPB())\n+                        pick_and_renumber(selected_option, starting_number, _NoOpPB(), dupe_mode=dupe_mode)\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Renumbering tool does not catch duplicate values\n## Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe\nI noticed that the renumber tool, does not catch duplicate values, it will instead just change the duplicated value to the next in sequence value. (I.e i have a door already placed, and tagged as 1. I start the renumber function and set an untagged door as door 1, it will automatically re-tag the door 1 as door 2 instead of indicating that there is a duplicate value.)\n\n## Describe the solution you'd like\nHere may be likely shift-click behavior options -\n1. an alert popup telling people (Duplicate Element Found) [default]\n2. Skip an Item if it is already renumbered [likely most used]\n3. sweep and renumber everything [likely less desirable]\n\n## Additional context\nI can see that this may cause some issues if, for example I am tagging hundreds of doors and it then starts changing tags for doors that should stay associated unless I am clicking to renumber it.\n\n", "hints_text": "It is in our radar from a previous issue. being tracked for future inclusion.\nThe point is to set a Shift+Click to give the users some options, however a major part of the functions needs to be rewritten.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "It is in our radar from a previous issue. being tracked for future inclusion.\nThe point is to set a Shift+Click to give the users some options, however a major part of the functions needs to be rewritten.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/0bffde6d17fd7410c73af458e9250bafaa3bddfb", "https://github.com/pyrevitlabs/pyRevit/commit/60843e7b9802e5c7cae5fe143dcaf1e3194fe683"], "created_at": "2026-02-22T19:05:51Z"}
{"repo": "pyrevitlabs/pyRevit", "pull_number": 2904, "instance_id": "pyrevitlabs__pyRevit-2904", "issue_numbers": [2891, 2902], "base_commit": "eb16048cd447b8ed1ef0f76ee3dd4ff24ebe8cc1", "patch": "diff --git a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\nindex 5c9862f232..0f46cd09a3 100644\n--- a/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\n+++ b/extensions/pyRevitTools.extension/pyRevit.tab/Analysis.panel/ColorSplasher.pushbutton/script.py\n@@ -127,8 +127,32 @@ def Execute(self, uiapp):\n             if not view:\n                 return\n             solid_fill_id = solid_fill_pattern_id()\n+\n+            # Get current category and parameter selection\n+            sel_cat = wndw._categories.SelectedItem[\"Value\"]\n+            if sel_cat == 0:\n+                return\n+\n+            # Find which parameter is currently checked\n+            checked_param = None\n+            for indx in range(wndw._list_box1.Items.Count):\n+                if wndw._list_box1.GetItemChecked(indx):\n+                    checked_param = wndw._list_box1.Items[indx][\"Value\"]\n+                    break\n+\n+            if checked_param is None:\n+                return\n+\n+            # Refresh element-to-value mappings to reflect current parameter values\n+            refreshed_values = get_range_values(sel_cat, checked_param, view)\n+\n+            # Create a mapping of value strings to user-selected colors\n+            color_map = {}\n+            for indx in range(wndw.list_box2.Items.Count):\n+                item = wndw.list_box2.Items[indx][\"Value\"]\n+                color_map[item.value] = (item.n1, item.n2, item.n3)\n+\n             with revit.Transaction(\"Apply colors to elements\"):\n-                sel_cat = wndw._categories.SelectedItem[\"Value\"]\n              